My Kid Could Paint That;;78;;94;;PG-13;;After watching her dad paint, 4-year-old Marla Olmstead decides she'd like to be a painter too. Showing remarkable facility, she's soon got paintings hanging in a local coffee shop and a handful of interested buyers. A local paper picks up the story, followed by the New York Times, and overnight Marla is hailed as a child prodigy. But not everybody is convinced that Marla painted the works alone. In the wake of a "60 Minutes" piece about her, it begins to look more and more like she had help.;;Documentary,Mystery & thriller;;Amir Bar-Lev;;2007;;Amir Bar-Lev,Elizabeth Cohen,Jonathan Crosby,Tara Sands;;https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/my_kid_could_paint_that